WEBVTT

00:01.479 --> 00:03.438
ADULT ADAM: Back in the '80s, before social media,

00:03.481 --> 00:05.092
the only way
to show off your family

00:05.135 --> 00:06.876
was with your annual
holiday card.

00:06.919 --> 00:08.660
Yep. Matching sweaters
and smiles

00:08.704 --> 00:10.967
sent to family and friends
near and far.

00:11.011 --> 00:13.187
My mom always had
a strong opinion.

00:13.230 --> 00:16.146
Who takes a picture
in a field of cornflowers?

00:16.190 --> 00:18.322
We all know this is the park
behind the interstate.

00:18.366 --> 00:20.672
No one thinks
you have a summer home.

00:20.716 --> 00:23.327
I'm gonna regret this,
but they seem pretty happy.

00:23.371 --> 00:25.242
Well, so do lobsters
before you boil them.

00:25.286 --> 00:26.722
Who's boiling
a lobster?

00:26.765 --> 00:28.158
Everyone,
shut your nog holes!

00:28.202 --> 00:29.768
Look at the Kremps'
Christmas card.

00:29.812 --> 00:31.292
[ANGELIC MUSIC PLAYS]

00:31.335 --> 00:33.598
POPS: They're literally
glowing.

00:33.642 --> 00:36.601
They look like the Kennedys...
But with no Teds.

00:36.645 --> 00:39.039
These beautiful blond turds
are not gonna outdo me
this year.

00:39.082 --> 00:40.605
Uh-uh. No.

00:40.649 --> 00:43.608
The Goldbergs are having
a professional
holiday photo taken.

00:43.652 --> 00:45.175
Nah.
No "nah."

00:45.219 --> 00:47.569
You can't "nah."
I "nah" your "nah."

00:47.612 --> 00:50.311
Murray's right.
You can't just force us
to take a photo

00:50.354 --> 00:53.618
out of some sort of
vindictive personal
jealousy.

00:53.662 --> 00:55.533
That's why all photos
are taken.

00:55.577 --> 00:57.318
Except you're forgetting
one thing.

00:57.361 --> 00:59.798
ADULT ADAM:
Yep. We had our own
crazy holiday cards.

00:59.842 --> 01:02.192
But the matching outfits and
stupid poses hid the fact

01:02.236 --> 01:04.368
that every single session
was torture.

01:04.412 --> 01:06.153
It looks like a yearbook
for an insane asylum.

01:06.196 --> 01:08.111
Ha!
He got you good, Bevy.

01:08.155 --> 01:10.244
Hey, kid, I like
having you around.

01:10.287 --> 01:11.854
Thanks, I guess.
I'm your son
who lives here,

01:11.897 --> 01:13.334
so it's a little weird.

01:13.377 --> 01:14.944
No, no, no.
The full package.

01:14.987 --> 01:16.772
No expenses spared.
[CHUCKLES] All right.

01:16.815 --> 01:17.903
[TELEPHONE CLACKS]

01:17.947 --> 01:20.123
I booked studio time.
Yay!

01:20.167 --> 01:22.343
Damn it!
Why'd I choose
to have a family?

01:22.386 --> 01:24.475
[DOOR OPENS]
Guess who's home
for winter break!

01:24.519 --> 01:26.303
It's Erica,
and she brought me
and laundry.

01:26.347 --> 01:27.957
Yep, I'm back,
and it's time

01:28.000 --> 01:29.785
not to reconnect
or catch up at all.

01:29.828 --> 01:31.656
I'm just gonna sleep
and do nothing.

01:31.700 --> 01:33.571
Not nothing,
'cause Mom's making us
take a family photo.

01:33.615 --> 01:35.269
Oh, no.

01:35.312 --> 01:37.227
You never saw me!
[DOOR CLOSES]

01:37.271 --> 01:41.057
'Tis the season to
pre-treat some stains
for my lady love.

01:41.101 --> 01:43.059
You need to do some
self-reflecting, kid.

01:43.103 --> 01:45.061
Oh, I'm going down!

01:45.105 --> 01:47.019
♪ I'm twisted up inside

01:47.063 --> 01:49.718
♪ But nonetheless,
I feel the need to say

01:52.851 --> 01:54.418
♪ I don't know the future

01:54.462 --> 01:58.379
♪ But the past keeps getting
clearer every day ♪

01:58.422 --> 02:00.424
ADULT ADAM:
It was December 11th,
1980-something,

02:00.468 --> 02:01.904
and the JTP were
preparing

02:01.947 --> 02:04.341
for their first holiday
together as roommates.

02:04.385 --> 02:05.777
GEORGE: Merry Christmas!

02:05.821 --> 02:07.649
Merry Christmas, George!
Merry Christmas!

02:07.692 --> 02:09.651
I love
It's a Wonderful Life.

02:09.694 --> 02:11.131
It reminds me
it is a wonderful life.[DOOR OPENS]

02:11.174 --> 02:12.436
ADULT ADAM:
Of course, one roommate

02:12.480 --> 02:14.177
didn't quite have
the holiday spirit.

02:14.221 --> 02:17.006
Turn the black-and-white
nonsense off.

02:17.049 --> 02:19.400
I demand we watch
a true holiday classic...

02:19.443 --> 02:21.097
Lone Wolf McQuade.

02:21.141 --> 02:22.359
Is that even
a holiday movie?

02:22.403 --> 02:23.665
Totally.

02:23.708 --> 02:26.320
It stars a jolly bearded man,
Chuck Norris,

02:26.363 --> 02:28.974
who delivers joy to children
by killing drug kingpins.

02:29.018 --> 02:30.367
So, that's a no.

02:30.411 --> 02:31.847
Time to kick our eyes
with some action.

02:31.890 --> 02:34.850
Human remote!

02:34.893 --> 02:36.852
[EXHALES SHAKILY]
That was my copy of
Lone Wolf McQuade.

02:36.895 --> 02:39.071
Uh, we've been talking
and feel you could

02:39.115 --> 02:41.683
be a little more...
Respectful of our stuff.

02:41.726 --> 02:44.164
When am I disrespectful,
stupid Matt Bradley?

02:44.207 --> 02:46.427
For instance, you constantly
use my toothbrush.

02:46.470 --> 02:47.863
To clean the shower,
so you're welcome.

02:47.906 --> 02:48.994
And every time
I get home from work,

02:49.038 --> 02:50.170
you "ninja surprise" me

02:50.213 --> 02:51.823
with a bo staff
to the belly.

02:51.867 --> 02:52.998
I thought
you were a burglar.

02:53.042 --> 02:54.435
Six times?

02:54.478 --> 02:56.045
And you ate
my allergy medicine.

02:56.088 --> 02:57.481
I regret that one.
Tasted real bad.

02:57.525 --> 02:59.048
So, you're gonna
change your ways

02:59.091 --> 03:00.136
and become
a better roommate?

03:00.180 --> 03:01.703
Over some ticky-tack stuff,

03:01.746 --> 03:03.183
like wearing your shirts

03:03.226 --> 03:05.315
and socks and underwear?
What?

03:05.359 --> 03:06.882
Plus, when we talk,
you always interrupt...

03:06.925 --> 03:08.318
Silence, okay?

03:08.362 --> 03:10.451
You've made
your mediocre case, JTP,

03:10.494 --> 03:12.714
and since it's the season
of forgiveness,

03:12.757 --> 03:14.716
you'll be happy to know
I forgive you

03:14.759 --> 03:17.197
for attacking me
in my own home.

03:17.240 --> 03:19.590
I apologize for using
this language,

03:19.634 --> 03:21.940
but Barry's
a crummy roommate.

03:21.984 --> 03:23.464
It's like no matter
what we say,

03:23.507 --> 03:24.987
he still wears
our underwear.

03:25.030 --> 03:26.771
Tasty needs to be stopped.

03:26.815 --> 03:29.339
ADULT ADAM:
As the JTP wished
Barry would chill out,

03:29.383 --> 03:31.428
my mom was firing up
the Festival of Lights.

03:31.472 --> 03:32.690
And amen.

03:32.734 --> 03:34.736
[BLOWS]

03:34.779 --> 03:36.912
We just had to sit through
all that Hebrew jibber-jabber.

03:36.955 --> 03:38.348
Now where's our presents?

03:38.392 --> 03:40.263
Gotta start off Hanukkah
with a bang.

03:40.307 --> 03:42.222
Tube socks! Tube socks!
Tube socks!

03:42.265 --> 03:45.355
Hoo! These stripey bad boys
will fit in all my shoes.

03:45.399 --> 03:47.923
As your romantic partner,
the sock excitement
isn't working for me.

03:47.966 --> 03:49.229
I'm gonna do better.

03:49.272 --> 03:52.101
Now we discuss
the most important part
about Hanukkah.

03:52.144 --> 03:53.276
Our people's struggle?

03:53.320 --> 03:55.322
Boring!
Our family photo.

03:55.365 --> 03:56.758
That's still a thing
we're doing?

03:56.801 --> 03:59.717
Let these impossibly
colorful sweaters
be my answer.

03:59.761 --> 04:00.849
Socks and a sweater!

04:00.892 --> 04:02.372
It's no big deal.

04:02.416 --> 04:05.636
No way am I squeezing
into this itchy yarn vomit.

04:05.680 --> 04:07.029
I think
it's beautiful.

04:07.072 --> 04:08.596
Not just the sweaters,
but the fact

04:08.639 --> 04:09.988
that you're including me
in your holiday card.

04:10.032 --> 04:11.294
Yeah, that's not
what's happening here.

04:11.338 --> 04:13.253
Geoff,
that's Barry's sweater.Oh.

04:13.296 --> 04:15.124
But since you have it on,
could you do me a favor

04:15.167 --> 04:16.865
and do something
punchy and kicky

04:16.908 --> 04:19.302
so I can see if it
has enough elasticity
for my hyper monkey?

04:20.782 --> 04:22.436
What is that?

04:22.479 --> 04:24.264
Okay, well, clearly,
you're not into it,

04:24.307 --> 04:26.353
so why don't you
just take it off,
and I'll put it on the dog.

04:27.136 --> 04:28.442
Sure.

04:28.485 --> 04:30.270
Well, I hope you guys
enjoy your...

04:30.313 --> 04:32.054
Family photo.

04:32.097 --> 04:33.577
Erica, I think
your boyfriend wants

04:33.621 --> 04:35.753
to be in our family
for some reason.

04:35.797 --> 04:37.233
That makes me sad.

04:37.277 --> 04:38.930
It makes us all sad,
buddy.

04:40.323 --> 04:42.717
Dude,
my mom's down there
trying to talk Pops

04:42.760 --> 04:44.806
into being the top
of our human pyramid.

04:44.849 --> 04:46.155
Is this really
what you want
to be a part of?

04:46.198 --> 04:47.591
I'm not married
to a pyramid,

04:47.635 --> 04:48.897
but some sort of
people-stacking
with your family

04:48.940 --> 04:50.594
is what I want.

04:50.638 --> 04:51.943
I mean, we've been dating
for years now,

04:51.987 --> 04:53.293
and I'm with your family
all the time,

04:53.336 --> 04:54.642
and now we're
living together.

04:54.685 --> 04:57.819
That last thing being
our very carefully
guarded secret.

04:57.862 --> 05:00.561
I know.
And it might be corny,
but it's what I want.

05:00.604 --> 05:03.607
Geoff, you're such a sweet
and sensitive boy,

05:03.651 --> 05:06.306
which is why I say this
in the gentlest way possible.

05:06.349 --> 05:07.568
Don't be a [BLEEP] idiot.
[GASPS]

05:07.611 --> 05:09.526
Not in front of
Bear-rah Fawcett!Okay.

05:09.570 --> 05:10.788
[BEAR THUDS]

05:10.832 --> 05:12.964
You need to accept
it's not gonna happen.

05:13.008 --> 05:14.705
Why not?
It's my parents.

05:14.749 --> 05:16.664
They're just old-fashioned
that way.

05:16.707 --> 05:18.274
Well, then I guess I'll just
have to get your family

05:18.318 --> 05:20.320
to see what
they're missing out on.
My Geoffer-vescence.

05:20.363 --> 05:21.582
Super bubbly.

05:21.625 --> 05:23.497
But it's best
to just sit this one out.

05:23.540 --> 05:25.673
But that photo pyramid
sounds so fun.

05:25.716 --> 05:28.763
I just want so badly
to be under your dad
or on top of your grandpa.

05:28.806 --> 05:30.852
[GAGS]

05:30.895 --> 05:32.810
I-I know
you don't know why,

05:32.854 --> 05:36.379
but we are not gonna
kiss for a while.

05:36.423 --> 05:38.903
ADULT ADAM: While Geoff was stressing out he couldn't be in the picture,

05:38.947 --> 05:41.863
Dave Kim and I were relaxing with a neighborhood stroll...

05:41.906 --> 05:43.168
Until this happened.
[TIRES SQUEAL]

05:43.212 --> 05:45.127
[TIRES SCREECH]

05:45.170 --> 05:46.389
[SCREAMING]

05:49.740 --> 05:50.828
Tell no one,
or I'll erase your bloodline!

05:50.872 --> 05:52.221
[TIRES SQUEAL]

05:52.264 --> 05:53.440
[SCREAMING CONTINUES]

05:53.483 --> 05:55.920
[SCREAMING] Oh!

05:55.964 --> 05:57.661
Holy crap!

05:57.705 --> 05:59.794
Why'd you guys snatch me
off the street like that?

05:59.837 --> 06:01.012
What a rush!

06:01.056 --> 06:02.449
Now I get why
kidnappers like this.

06:02.492 --> 06:03.754
Super awesome
and dramatic, right?

06:03.798 --> 06:05.626
Again, why am I here?

06:05.669 --> 06:07.454
Well, we figured
you lived with Barry

06:07.497 --> 06:09.107
your whole life
basically problem-free.

06:09.151 --> 06:11.109
And since you know
how to handle him
better than anybody,

06:11.153 --> 06:13.111
we thought you'd
have some suggestions
on how to prank him.

06:13.155 --> 06:15.462
You couldn't have
just lobbed in a phone call?

06:15.505 --> 06:16.854
Gah!

06:16.898 --> 06:18.682
[SIGHS] Fine.

06:18.726 --> 06:20.162
Tell me how bad
you wanna hurt him.

06:20.205 --> 06:22.338
Well, he's rude,
inconsiderate,
and destructive.

06:22.382 --> 06:24.906
He did unspeakable things
in my BVDs.Say no more.

06:24.949 --> 06:26.603
He soggied
my cotton bottoms.

06:26.647 --> 06:28.039
What part of "no more"
don't you understand?

06:28.083 --> 06:29.867
He freckled
my Fruit of the Looms.I get it.

06:29.911 --> 06:31.173
He skidded my scanties!

06:31.216 --> 06:33.088
I have a full picture!

06:33.131 --> 06:35.264
Just take away the thing
Barry loves most.

06:35.307 --> 06:36.352
Caramel?
Knock-knock jokes?

06:36.396 --> 06:38.702
Apples with caramel?
For sure caramel.

06:38.746 --> 06:42.010
But more specifically,
himself.

06:42.053 --> 06:43.707
Oh, nice.
Of course.

06:43.751 --> 06:45.100
Could you be
even more specific?

06:45.143 --> 06:46.231
Yeah.
Yeah.

06:46.275 --> 06:47.581
Barry's ego is so big.

06:47.624 --> 06:49.583
If you want
to get back at him,

06:49.626 --> 06:50.671
make him feel like
he doesn't matter.

06:50.714 --> 06:52.716
You mean erase him
from existence,

06:52.760 --> 06:54.239
like George Bailey in
It's a Wonderful Life.

06:54.283 --> 06:55.632
Yeah.

06:55.676 --> 06:56.807
ADULT ADAM:
And so, the next day,

06:56.851 --> 06:59.723
the JTP played
the meanest prank ever...

06:59.767 --> 07:01.116
They pretended Barry
didn't exist.

07:01.159 --> 07:03.248
BARRY: Morning, JTP.

07:03.292 --> 07:06.513
Who wants to start this day
by tossing this bowling ball
I found off the roof?

07:06.556 --> 07:08.036
Can we help you,
stranger?

07:08.079 --> 07:10.168
You seem to have wandered
into the wrong house.

07:10.212 --> 07:12.301
Don't be stupid,
stupid Matt Bradley.
It's me.

07:12.344 --> 07:13.476
And you are...

07:13.520 --> 07:14.564
What?

07:14.608 --> 07:16.871
It's me. Big Tasty.

07:16.914 --> 07:19.090
Your charismatic
and angry leader

07:19.134 --> 07:20.701
who doesn't like
to be questioned

07:20.744 --> 07:22.137
before his morning
Hawaiian Punch.

07:22.180 --> 07:23.965
Take it easy, okay?

07:24.008 --> 07:25.445
W-We just
don't know you.

07:25.488 --> 07:28.578
Of course you do,
you ship-in-a-bottle
captain, Andy.

07:28.622 --> 07:30.058
Look at the photo of us
inside the...

07:30.101 --> 07:32.321
♪♪

07:32.364 --> 07:34.541
What? Where's my gorgeous face
and rugged features?

07:34.584 --> 07:37.369
Not in that picture
of the J.A.G...

07:37.413 --> 07:39.154
The Jenkintown
Association of Guys.

07:39.197 --> 07:40.851
J.A.G.

07:40.895 --> 07:42.374
ALL: J.A.G.!

07:42.418 --> 07:44.507
Hello, male peers
and roommates.

07:44.551 --> 07:47.423
I live here.
This is my beloved home.

07:47.467 --> 07:49.381
Johnny Atkins isn't a part
of our friend group.

07:49.425 --> 07:50.861
He's more than
just a part of it.

07:50.905 --> 07:52.863
He's our emotionally
in-control leader.

07:52.907 --> 07:55.344
This is my beloved home.
I live here.

07:55.387 --> 07:58.782
I demand you explain what
is happening right now, JTP.

07:58.826 --> 08:01.089
What's happening is,
we don't know who you are,

08:01.132 --> 08:03.134
and you're not demonstrating
the calm and cool

08:03.178 --> 08:04.875
the J.A.G.
is known for.

08:04.919 --> 08:06.790
Oh, my God.
[SIGHS]

08:06.834 --> 08:08.183
There's only one explanation
for this.

08:08.226 --> 08:09.880
You realize
the error of your ways

08:09.924 --> 08:11.360
and you're ready
to treat your roommates

08:11.403 --> 08:12.622
with kindness and respect?

08:12.666 --> 08:14.232
I've been erased
from history.

08:14.276 --> 08:15.277
Oh, boy.
That's your takeaway?

08:15.320 --> 08:17.932
My dominance
was never born.

08:17.975 --> 08:20.500
Oh, he is taking this
way harder than I thought.

08:20.543 --> 08:23.154
Johnny Atkins is
second-guessing his role
in this hateful prank.

08:23.198 --> 08:24.678
Prank?
What's he talking about?

08:24.721 --> 08:27.376
I'm talking about how
your closest friends
bought me tacos

08:27.419 --> 08:29.334
to question your
existential value
in the world.

08:29.378 --> 08:31.641
I don't know
what that means,
but...JTP?

08:31.685 --> 08:33.208
ALL: JTP.

08:33.251 --> 08:34.688
Bud, it was a prank,

08:34.731 --> 08:36.254
like how you sullied
my under-khakis.

08:36.298 --> 08:37.386
Uh, now we're even.

08:37.429 --> 08:39.910
I merely wore
your most intimate apparel.

08:39.954 --> 08:41.912
You stole my place
in this world.

08:41.956 --> 08:44.828
The important thing is,
we can resume our lives
and put this to rest.

08:44.872 --> 08:47.352
Opposite.
I'm coming for you guys.

08:47.396 --> 08:49.441
It may not be
today or tomorrow,

08:49.485 --> 08:51.182
'cause I got
some stuff to do,

08:51.226 --> 08:53.141
but it'll be sometime
convenient for me,

08:53.184 --> 08:54.359
probably Wednesday,

08:54.403 --> 08:57.188
and it will ruin
your lives forever.

08:57.232 --> 08:59.626
ADULT ADAM: While Barry
was dead set on revenge,

08:59.669 --> 09:02.716
Geoff was dead set on being
part of our family photo.

09:02.759 --> 09:05.632
Why is this meshugenah
blocking the tube?

09:05.675 --> 09:08.199
I want to see if Simon
makes up with Simon.

09:08.243 --> 09:10.680
I stand before you with
a comprehensive presentation

09:10.724 --> 09:12.203
of why I should be
in your family photo.

09:12.247 --> 09:13.770
I'm not looking
at any of that.

09:13.814 --> 09:15.555
And I knew you wouldn't,
because,
as a fixture in this home,

09:15.598 --> 09:16.643
I know everything about you.

09:16.686 --> 09:18.296
Then you know
I'm irritated.

09:18.340 --> 09:20.037
Which is why I brought you
a bacon and egg sandwich

09:20.081 --> 09:21.822
with a side of another
bacon and egg sandwich.

09:21.865 --> 09:23.693
Eh. Do what you do,
egg man.

09:23.737 --> 09:26.566
Geoff, stop.
You are an important part
of this family,

09:26.609 --> 09:28.568
and I'm sorry I didn't ask you
to be in the picture.

09:29.699 --> 09:30.700
You're in.

09:31.701 --> 09:32.789
Oh, my God.

09:32.833 --> 09:34.399
This is such
a big moment for me.

09:34.443 --> 09:35.487
I don't even know
what to say.

09:35.531 --> 09:37.054
Say you'll pull it
together.

09:37.098 --> 09:39.013
I don't need you puffy
for when we take the pic

09:39.056 --> 09:41.537
that will devastate that
Christmas clown Jinzy Kremp.

09:41.581 --> 09:42.973
I'm the favorite
holiday boy now.

09:43.017 --> 09:44.801
Let me see
your pearly whites, huh?

09:44.845 --> 09:46.498
Oh, yeah.
Those are gonna
shine up nicely.

09:46.542 --> 09:48.326
Uh, what's going on
in here?

09:48.370 --> 09:50.459
Your mom's inspecting
your boyfriend

09:50.502 --> 09:52.461
like he's some kind
of show pony.

09:52.504 --> 09:54.332
It's invasive,
but I'm gonna be
in the photo!

09:54.376 --> 09:56.639
What? No.
You guys don't want him
in the photo, right?

09:56.683 --> 09:58.815
Fine by me.
Murray, you cool with it?

09:58.859 --> 10:01.122
I've never cared less
about anything in my life.

10:01.165 --> 10:02.906
We are going to be
on all the fridges

10:02.950 --> 10:05.126
and mantels
throughout the suburbs.
It's happening!

10:05.169 --> 10:07.084
[CHUCKLES]
It really is.

10:07.128 --> 10:08.477
So, so fast.

10:08.520 --> 10:10.435
♪♪

10:13.177 --> 10:14.744
ADULT ADAM: The JTP
had made Barry feel

10:14.788 --> 10:16.354
like he didn't even exist...
[DOOR SLAMS]

10:16.398 --> 10:17.921
...so he was determined
to get back at them

10:17.965 --> 10:19.706
in a way they would
remember forever.

10:19.749 --> 10:21.055
[SIGHS] Where do we keep
the rat poison?

10:21.098 --> 10:22.839
Oh, no.
Do we have a rat?

10:22.883 --> 10:23.927
Three.

10:23.971 --> 10:25.712
My friends
hurtfully pranked me,

10:25.755 --> 10:27.757
and now I want to even more
hurtfully prank them back.

10:27.801 --> 10:30.368
With poison?
Hilarious, I know,

10:30.412 --> 10:33.937
but I'm open to suggestions,
just as long as it's something

10:33.981 --> 10:36.157
that destroys their lives
and forever changes us all.

10:36.200 --> 10:37.637
Every week,
I caution you

10:37.680 --> 10:40.422
with advice
in difficult situations.

10:40.465 --> 10:41.641
It's basically
all you do,

10:41.684 --> 10:43.338
besides snarf down
our baked goods.

10:43.381 --> 10:46.471
No matter my advice,
you do the exact opposite.

10:46.515 --> 10:48.082
I am a little
frustrating.

10:48.125 --> 10:50.301
So, I'm gonna
give you bad advice

10:50.345 --> 10:53.174
in the hopes that you'll do
the right thing.Getting bored.

10:53.217 --> 10:56.177
Destroy your buddies
with extreme malice.

10:56.220 --> 10:58.962
So, you're kinda saying
I shouldn't seek revenge

10:59.006 --> 11:01.399
because it will irreparably
damage my friendships?

11:01.443 --> 11:02.923
Wait, are you
really hearing me?

11:02.966 --> 11:04.011
Who knows?

11:04.054 --> 11:05.752
♪♪

11:05.795 --> 11:09.016
[AIR HORN BLARES]

11:09.059 --> 11:10.800
Good morning,
tired amigos.

11:10.844 --> 11:13.020
What's with the horn, man?
It's 6:00 a.m.

11:13.063 --> 11:15.196
Apologies have no sense
of time or place.

11:15.239 --> 11:16.632
Oh, good.

11:16.676 --> 11:18.112
You're here to acknowledge
the error of your ways,

11:18.155 --> 11:19.200
and you're ready
to move forward

11:19.243 --> 11:21.332
as an equal respectful partner
in our home.

11:21.376 --> 11:22.769
Something like that.

11:22.812 --> 11:24.248
I even brought you all
holiday gifts.

11:24.292 --> 11:25.902
I don't understand.

11:25.946 --> 11:27.904
You were super angry
and irrational yesterday.

11:27.948 --> 11:30.124
But then my wise
old grandpa suggested

11:30.167 --> 11:31.908
I stop this senseless
cycle of pranking.

11:31.952 --> 11:34.345
Good advice.
What's in the boxes, Barry?

11:34.389 --> 11:36.521
Just a little reminder
of how I feel about you guys.

11:36.565 --> 11:38.001
Ah, screw it.
I'm going in.

11:38.045 --> 11:39.176
[CHUCKLES]

11:40.351 --> 11:41.962
My dress slacks?
[CHUCKLES]

11:42.005 --> 11:43.050
They're shredded.

11:43.093 --> 11:44.181
You've been pranked!

11:44.225 --> 11:46.227
I've got my sister's
engagement dinner tonight.

11:46.270 --> 11:48.577
I guess you'll have to hit
the boys section of Sears.

11:48.620 --> 11:49.709
Dude, that's not a gift.

11:49.752 --> 11:51.449
That's just mean
and destructive.

11:51.493 --> 11:52.537
You're up next,
Naked Rob.

11:54.278 --> 11:56.933
My Nudist Enthusiast
magazines?

11:56.977 --> 11:58.761
These are expensive
and European.

11:58.805 --> 12:00.589
Now they're confetti.

12:00.632 --> 12:02.330
I had to learn French
for these.

12:02.373 --> 12:04.724
Finally, for my favorite
person in the world,

12:04.767 --> 12:06.769
stupid Matt Bradley.

12:06.813 --> 12:08.162
I don't wanna open mine.
Your instincts are good.

12:09.685 --> 12:11.600
Is this
my birth certificate

12:11.643 --> 12:13.384
or the last letter
my grandfather wrote me?

12:13.428 --> 12:16.387
Those are your last
three paychecks
from The Gap.

12:16.431 --> 12:18.215
Now I don't have money
for presents for my family.

12:18.259 --> 12:20.783
[CHUCKLES] It's even funnier
than I thought! Whoo!

12:20.827 --> 12:22.698
Dude,
this is way too far.

12:22.742 --> 12:24.613
Yeah, you made
Matt Bradley weep.

12:24.656 --> 12:26.310
[VOICE BREAKING]
I actually cry every day,

12:26.354 --> 12:27.747
but this one hurt.

12:27.790 --> 12:29.096
Barry, you need
to get out.

12:29.139 --> 12:30.793
Because I brought
our prank war

12:30.837 --> 12:32.490
to its naturally
devastating conclusion?

12:32.534 --> 12:34.014
You're not just
a horrible roommate.

12:34.057 --> 12:35.406
You're a horrible friend.

12:35.450 --> 12:37.582
[NORMAL VOICE]
We're gonna go
grab breakfast.

12:37.626 --> 12:39.497
When we get back,
you need to be gone.

12:39.541 --> 12:41.891
No! Guys, come back.

12:41.935 --> 12:43.501
How will I learn
if you don't

12:43.545 --> 12:45.329
immediately forgive me
and move on?

12:45.373 --> 12:47.244
ADULT ADAM:
As Barry couldn't see
the error of his ways,

12:47.288 --> 12:49.333
the next day,
Geoff was about to witness

12:49.377 --> 12:52.336
a traditional Goldberg family holiday card catastrophe.

12:52.380 --> 12:54.251
Oh, my God!

12:54.295 --> 12:56.297
My scrumptious family
looks amazing.

12:56.340 --> 12:59.691
Paul, is it true that when
a family looks this pretty,

12:59.735 --> 13:01.519
you pay them
to take their picture?

13:01.563 --> 13:03.043
No.

13:03.086 --> 13:06.002
Okay, Goldberg clan.
Let's see those smiles.

13:06.046 --> 13:09.527
Uh, young man in the back?
You look really sad.

13:09.571 --> 13:10.354
My boy friends
dumped me.

13:11.573 --> 13:13.183
So it begins.

13:13.227 --> 13:14.619
You know, we might as well
just cut our losses

13:14.663 --> 13:16.230
and head on home.
No way.

13:16.273 --> 13:18.536
All right, come on.
Smile for Mama, Barry.

13:18.580 --> 13:19.842
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]
Oh, no!

13:19.886 --> 13:21.975
Barry's grimace
doesn't express
family unity and joy.

13:22.018 --> 13:24.107
Nope. His stink face
is the least of it.

13:24.151 --> 13:25.761
My grandpa can't
stand this long.

13:25.805 --> 13:27.458
Hey, Pops,
how ya feeling?

13:27.502 --> 13:29.721
All my fluids
are in my feet.

13:29.765 --> 13:32.072
I-I-I think
I'll lie down
for a minute.

13:32.115 --> 13:33.160
Oh!

13:33.203 --> 13:34.552
Dad, what the hell
are you doing?

13:34.596 --> 13:37.077
You got a pillow
or a couch cushion?

13:37.120 --> 13:39.383
Oh, no!
Your grandpa just made
the ground his bed!

13:39.427 --> 13:41.342
It's what he does.
All right.

13:41.385 --> 13:43.126
Just like how my dad
always gets overheated.

13:43.170 --> 13:44.867
Hey, Mur-Man,
how's that sweater
treating you?

13:44.911 --> 13:46.129
Make it stop!
Get it off!

13:46.173 --> 13:47.783
Just keep clicking.
We'll get one.

13:47.827 --> 13:50.264
Maybe even one
with some fun props?
What do you say, Ad?

13:50.307 --> 13:51.787
Who screams
holiday cheer more

13:51.831 --> 13:54.137
than flamboyant pop icon
Elton John?

13:54.181 --> 13:56.705
Are we sleeping
or pop stars?
Let's pick a lane!

13:56.748 --> 13:57.924
Pull it together,
Geoff.

13:57.967 --> 13:59.403
Please tell me
you're getting
some keepers.

13:59.447 --> 14:00.535
Definitely.

14:00.578 --> 14:02.102
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

14:02.145 --> 14:04.060
♪♪

14:05.322 --> 14:07.107
It all fell apart
so fast.

14:07.150 --> 14:08.586
Yeah,
I tried to tell you.

14:08.630 --> 14:10.284
Just be happy
you never have to
do this again.

14:11.807 --> 14:13.374
Okay,
I think we got it.

14:13.417 --> 14:15.115
ADULT ADAM: But we didn't.

14:15.158 --> 14:16.812
Back at home,
Barry still didn't get

14:16.856 --> 14:19.119
why he lost his place
in the JTP pad.

14:19.162 --> 14:21.251
You've been given
a great gift, George...

14:21.295 --> 14:23.819
A chance to see what
the world would
be like without you.

14:23.863 --> 14:26.039
I wish I had someone
old and wise

14:26.082 --> 14:27.562
who would guide me
through life.

14:27.605 --> 14:30.043
I'm going back
to focusing on Adam.

14:30.086 --> 14:32.306
Okay, Pops.
I'm gonna crash here tonight.

14:32.349 --> 14:34.830
Sure, there's 12 minutes left,
but let's turn it off.

14:34.874 --> 14:37.006
♪♪

14:40.662 --> 14:42.751
[YAWNS]

14:42.794 --> 14:44.709
[GASPS] This isn't
where I fell asleep.

14:44.753 --> 14:45.841
Oh, no!

14:45.885 --> 14:47.016
Have I been
gently kidnapped?

14:47.060 --> 14:49.714
Your body is right
where you left it.

14:49.758 --> 14:52.717
You're dreaming of
what the world would be like
if you didn't exist.

14:52.761 --> 14:54.589
This isn't
the JTP pad.

14:54.632 --> 14:55.851
It has no holes
in the wall.

14:55.895 --> 14:57.853
Of course
there's no holes.

14:57.897 --> 14:59.376
You weren't here
to punch them.

14:59.420 --> 15:00.464
[DOOR OPENS]

15:00.508 --> 15:01.770
Go for Mr. Bradley.

15:02.771 --> 15:04.642
"Mr. Bradley"?

15:04.686 --> 15:07.384
Who are you, your stepdad
that officially adopted you?

15:07.428 --> 15:08.472
Nerd.

15:08.516 --> 15:09.604
He can't hear you.

15:09.647 --> 15:12.650
And he's now a successful
Gap businessman.

15:12.694 --> 15:14.652
Without you making him
late for work,

15:14.696 --> 15:17.568
he became Worldwide Head
of Jean Shorts.

15:17.612 --> 15:19.005
Buy! Sell!

15:19.048 --> 15:19.919
Business!
Huh?

15:21.224 --> 15:23.009
Oh, hey, there, friend.

15:23.052 --> 15:24.706
How's the weather
up here, you ask?

15:24.749 --> 15:26.316
[CHUCKLING]
Why, it's great,

15:26.360 --> 15:29.711
because life
for the very tall
always is.

15:29.754 --> 15:31.191
[LAUGHS]
Who stretched Andy?

15:31.234 --> 15:32.409
No one.

15:32.453 --> 15:35.891
Without you
stealing his lunch,
Andy had a growth spurt.

15:35.935 --> 15:39.982
He's been helping people
grab things off the top shelf
ever since.

15:40.635 --> 15:42.245
Afternoon, gents.

15:42.289 --> 15:43.812
Gorgeous Rob!
Gorgeous Rob!

15:43.855 --> 15:45.292
"Gorgeous" Rob?

15:45.335 --> 15:47.163
You're Naked Rob,
and that's all you'll ever be.

15:47.207 --> 15:50.036
Without you to pants Rob
in second grade,

15:50.079 --> 15:52.821
Naked Rob
never came to be.

15:52.864 --> 15:54.997
He built his identity
based on a love

15:55.041 --> 15:58.000
of high-quality
Italian menswear.

15:58.044 --> 15:59.393
Hope you guys don't mind.

15:59.436 --> 16:02.004
I brought a party sub.
And a party.

16:03.005 --> 16:04.659
ANDY: It's our wives,

16:04.702 --> 16:06.704
who cherish us
not just for our success,

16:06.748 --> 16:08.750
but for our high
self-esteem.

16:08.793 --> 16:10.708
Let's kiss them
and watch football.

16:10.752 --> 16:12.623
Yeah.
No! No!

16:12.667 --> 16:15.017
You don't have wives!
You have me!

16:15.061 --> 16:17.759
And I matter!
I make your lives better!

16:17.802 --> 16:20.327
♪♪

16:20.370 --> 16:22.111
Gah!

16:22.155 --> 16:24.505
That Wonderful Lifemovie
taught me I need
to fix everything!

16:24.548 --> 16:26.898
But you were asleep
for 10 seconds!

16:26.942 --> 16:29.162
I've been asleep
my whole life.

16:29.205 --> 16:31.425
So George Bailey,
you listen to.

16:31.468 --> 16:34.297
What?
Your name is Al something.

16:34.341 --> 16:35.951
Anyway, I gotta go.

16:35.995 --> 16:38.258
ADULT ADAM: While Barry
ran off to save
his friendships,

16:38.301 --> 16:40.303
Geoff was about to run
into my sister at the mall.

16:40.347 --> 16:41.435
Erica?

16:41.478 --> 16:43.132
Geoff, what are
you doing here?

16:43.176 --> 16:45.526
I thought I'd get your family
a little thank-you
for including me.

16:45.569 --> 16:46.788
Hey, Geoff.

16:46.831 --> 16:49.356
Oh, you'll be happy to know
that Jinzy will be

16:49.399 --> 16:51.662
crying into her
nothing-flavored
holiday cookies

16:51.706 --> 16:53.099
because we nailed it.

16:53.142 --> 16:54.230
You took the photo
without me?

16:54.274 --> 16:57.581
Yes, 'cause they are
the worst... The worst.

16:57.625 --> 16:59.366
So, let's just rush away
and never speak of this again.

16:59.409 --> 17:01.716
Wait a minute.
We wanted Geoff
in the picture.

17:01.759 --> 17:03.805
You're the one who said
he had explosive diarrhea.

17:03.848 --> 17:06.286
What? No.

17:06.329 --> 17:07.852
And I definitely did not
say "explosive."

17:07.896 --> 17:09.985
You did,
and it read as true.

17:10.029 --> 17:11.900
Been there.
It's our people's burden.

17:11.943 --> 17:13.032
Shame only
makes it worse.

17:13.075 --> 17:15.077
I-I don't
have diarrhea.

17:15.121 --> 17:16.209
So, why?

17:16.252 --> 17:17.819
Uh...

17:17.862 --> 17:19.995
This is a guess,
but she definitely

17:20.039 --> 17:21.083
doesn't want you
to be in our picture.

17:21.127 --> 17:22.215
Is that true?

17:22.258 --> 17:23.477
Please, I can explain.

17:23.520 --> 17:24.956
No need.

17:25.000 --> 17:26.306
Enjoy being
with your family.

17:28.221 --> 17:30.092
Well, it's not
a Goldbergs holiday

17:30.136 --> 17:32.529
unless someone runs away upset
and possibly with diarrhea.

17:34.792 --> 17:37.230
ADULT ADAM:
Even though the JTP
had kicked Barry out,

17:37.273 --> 17:39.841
he was still determined to
pull off a holiday miracle.

17:39.884 --> 17:42.017
JTP, I have returned.

17:42.061 --> 17:43.540
I thought
we took your key.

17:43.584 --> 17:46.239
You did, but I made dozens
of copies of the JT-Key,

17:46.282 --> 17:48.415
all of which I lost,
except for this one.

17:48.458 --> 17:49.720
What do you want?
Just one thing...

17:49.764 --> 17:51.026
Your forgiveness.

17:51.070 --> 17:54.247
Oh! What's in the bag, man?
I think it just moved.

17:54.290 --> 17:56.336
It's definitely
full of spiders.I know what's in there.

17:56.379 --> 17:58.512
My greatest fear...
Speaking in public.

17:58.555 --> 17:59.730
BARRY: No.

17:59.774 --> 18:01.384
I had a dream
about you guys,

18:01.428 --> 18:04.083
and you were all better
and way more successful,
and I hated it.

18:04.126 --> 18:06.172
You hate the idea
of us being successful?

18:06.215 --> 18:08.478
I love the idea
of you guys crushing life.

18:08.522 --> 18:10.611
I just hated that
I wasn't a part of it.

18:10.654 --> 18:13.092
That's...
Really nice, Bar.

18:13.135 --> 18:15.355
So, I emptied
my bank account

18:15.398 --> 18:16.617
and replaced all the gifts
I shredded.

18:18.009 --> 18:19.098
Your pants.

18:20.316 --> 18:21.535
Your nudie mags.

18:21.578 --> 18:22.579
[CHUCKLES]

18:23.537 --> 18:24.407
And your paychecks.

18:25.191 --> 18:26.322
Whoa.

18:26.366 --> 18:28.368
They're all...
Kinda here.

18:28.411 --> 18:30.892
And I got a little something
extra for each of you.

18:30.935 --> 18:32.546
For Naked Rob,

18:32.589 --> 18:35.375
a Miami Vicesuit,
'cause in my dream,

18:35.418 --> 18:37.768
you looked amazing
with or without clothes.

18:37.812 --> 18:41.076
For Andy,
a 76ers Dr. J jersey,

18:41.120 --> 18:43.122
'cause you stand taller
than anyone I know.

18:43.165 --> 18:45.602
And for my dear friend
Matt Bradley,

18:45.646 --> 18:47.300
I got you nothing,

18:47.343 --> 18:48.823
'cause you're perfect
the way you are.

18:48.866 --> 18:49.954
You ran outta money?

18:49.998 --> 18:51.086
You're welcome.

18:51.130 --> 18:53.523
Get in here.
[LAUGHTER]

18:53.567 --> 18:55.351
ADULT ADAM: While Barry had
finally found his way,

18:55.395 --> 18:57.397
Geoff had never
felt more lost.

18:57.440 --> 18:58.876
Hey.

18:58.920 --> 19:01.009
Don't worry.
I'll be out of here soon.

19:01.052 --> 19:02.837
Geoff, stop.
You got it all wrong.

19:02.880 --> 19:04.360
No, I think
it's pretty clear.

19:04.404 --> 19:05.535
You're ashamed of me.

19:05.579 --> 19:07.102
What?
Yeah.

19:07.146 --> 19:09.452
You don't want me
in your permanent picture
for everyone to see

19:09.496 --> 19:11.150
because you're the cool,
hot girl

19:11.193 --> 19:12.629
and I'm just the sweet,
little puppy dog

19:12.673 --> 19:14.631
who follows you around
and folds your clothes,

19:14.675 --> 19:16.111
but when
it comes time to...

19:16.155 --> 19:18.113
[THE CURE'S PICTURES OF YOU
PLAYS]

19:18.157 --> 19:20.463
Geoff, I am never
ashamed of you.

19:20.507 --> 19:22.117
Never.

19:22.161 --> 19:23.945
There's nothing better
in my life than you.

19:23.988 --> 19:26.904
Then why can't I be
in your family's
stupid holiday card?

19:26.948 --> 19:29.255
Because...
I'm not ready.

19:29.298 --> 19:30.952
How does that
even make sense?

19:30.995 --> 19:32.345
It was your idea
to live together,

19:32.388 --> 19:33.824
secretly,
in this little room.

19:33.868 --> 19:36.175
And I am loving it.

19:36.218 --> 19:38.742
But you being in that picture
with my family,

19:38.786 --> 19:40.788
it made me anxious
about the future.

19:40.831 --> 19:42.181
The future?

19:42.224 --> 19:44.052
Our future.

19:44.095 --> 19:45.358
About getting married

19:45.401 --> 19:47.098
and starting
our own family

19:47.142 --> 19:48.274
and being together forever.

19:50.537 --> 19:52.626
♪ I've been living so long

19:52.669 --> 19:54.584
GEOFF: Barry and Lainey.

19:54.628 --> 19:57.761
You're scared this card will
be a permanent reminder of us
if things don't work out.

19:57.805 --> 19:59.807
All I know is,
right here, right now,

19:59.850 --> 20:02.679
I am so happy,

20:02.723 --> 20:06.074
and I don't want
to think about anything
beyond right now.

20:06.117 --> 20:07.510
I'm willing to take this
as slow as you want.

20:08.555 --> 20:09.773
But I'm starting
to think

20:09.817 --> 20:10.774
you might be right
about that photo.

20:10.818 --> 20:12.950
♪♪

20:12.994 --> 20:14.256
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]

20:14.300 --> 20:16.215
ADULT ADAM:
With that, Geoff got
a version of the photo

20:16.258 --> 20:18.217
he liked even more.
[CHUCKLES]

20:18.260 --> 20:20.480
That's the thing
about the holidays.

20:20.523 --> 20:22.003
They may not always turn out
like you'd imagined.

20:22.046 --> 20:23.222
[SIGHS]
It's not great.

20:25.833 --> 20:26.834
But it's us.

20:28.314 --> 20:29.532
You're right.
[CHUCKLES]

20:29.576 --> 20:31.404
♪ There was nothing
in the world ♪

20:31.447 --> 20:33.623
But then you're reminded
that the little
imperfections

20:33.667 --> 20:35.016
are what make life special,

20:35.059 --> 20:37.540
those moments between the
ones in all the pictures,

20:37.584 --> 20:39.629
the littles ones with
the real smiles.

20:39.673 --> 20:42.241
Those are the sweet spot.

20:42.284 --> 20:44.155
'Cause after all, in the end,

20:44.199 --> 20:45.896
when we learn to savor
those moments,

20:45.940 --> 20:47.811
the tiny snapshots,

20:47.855 --> 20:51.424
[CHUCKLES] Well,
it really is
a wonderful life.

20:51.467 --> 20:53.513
♪♪

20:53.556 --> 20:55.645
Let's see.
Everybody's nice and neat.

20:55.689 --> 20:57.212
Okay.
Let me get your tie.

20:57.256 --> 20:58.692
WOMAN: Adam needs
his hair combed.

20:58.735 --> 21:00.520
That's one
handsome boy here.

21:00.563 --> 21:01.695
[BELL DINGS]

21:04.393 --> 21:06.177
Oh, no! Not again!
[TIRES SQUEAL]

21:06.221 --> 21:08.354
Aah!

21:08.397 --> 21:10.225
ADAM: Barry?
Now you're in on this?

21:10.269 --> 21:12.793
I heard we had a new way
of getting information
out of you,

21:12.836 --> 21:14.316
and we need to know...

21:14.360 --> 21:16.362
Where's that deli
that lets you taste the meat
before you buy it?

21:16.405 --> 21:17.928
It's the one
on Main Street.

21:17.972 --> 21:19.147
[TIRES SCREECH]

21:19.190 --> 21:21.497
Is breakfast truly the most
important meal of the day?

21:21.541 --> 21:23.717
Is a frog an amphibian
or a reptile?

21:23.760 --> 21:26.285
Does Matt Bradley need
to go to the doctor for this?

21:27.503 --> 21:28.809
Sorry. Forgot what
I was gonna ask.

21:28.852 --> 21:29.549
Put the hood
back on him.
